90
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:53,358
It combines both classic aspects
of British sport, whimsy and restraint.

91
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:57,779
Oh! So restrained.

92
00:03:57,862 --> 00:04:00,365
I believe it was
Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain

93
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:02,533
who called croquet "barely a game."

94
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:07,372
It's kind of fun, I guess.
But can I teach you a different game?

95
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:11,960
You whack it as hard as you can,
in whatever direction you want.

96
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:13,753
Jaguars rule!

97
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,965
The Jaguars are very good!

98
00:04:17,048 --> 00:04:19,342
-Ooh!
-Whoa! Nice!

99
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:23,596
Mmm.

100
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:26,349
[laughing]

101
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:28,309
-Thor!
-Well done!

102
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:30,144
Okay. Here's where I am on this.

103
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,688
We gotta kill Derek.

104
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:33,564
No, think about it.

105
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:37,819
What if Vicky calls for Janet
and Derek shows up too?

106
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:40,154
She'll have questions we can't answer.

107
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:43,408
But Derek does seem to be helping Janet
get over Jason.

108
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:45,660
Right?
No earthquakes since he showed up.

109
00:04:45,743 --> 00:04:49,998
But if we get rid of Derek,
maybe Janet will start glitching again.

110
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:53,668
If we can't kill Derek,
we gotta break up Jason and Tahani.

111
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:57,338
If that relationship ends,
then Janet won't feel sad anymore

112
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,048
and maybe she'll get rid of Derek herself.

113
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:02,760
Girl, you are a messy bench
who loves drama and I am into it.

114
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:06,306
I'm sorry, Michael,
but that's also ethically dicey.

115
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:07,724
Here comes the egghead.

116
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:09,851
Jason and Tahani are happy together.

117
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:12,895
Telling them he was once married
to Janet might cause them harm.

118
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:16,149
It's not permissible
to ruin their happiness to save ourselves.

119
00:05:16,232 --> 00:05:20,278
But isn't keeping a secret
from someone basically like lying, though?

120
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:23,781
No, it's okay to keep a secret,
as long as it isn't harming anyone

121
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:26,200
and telling them that secret
might cause harm.

122
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:27,410
Noice!

123
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,037
Cool. Good point, egghead.

124
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,331
I'll tell you what else
would cause them harm,

125
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:34,292
getting caught
and sent to the real Bad Place

126
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,918
to be tortured for eternity,

127
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:38,671
which will happen
if Derek blows our cover.

128
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,549
I know! But we'll also be sent
to the real Bad Place

129
00:05:41,632 --> 00:05:43,134
if we do bad things.

130
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:47,305
I know it's tempting to take a shortcut,
but moral strength is defined

131
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:49,807
by how we behave in times of stress.

132
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,727
Has anyone ever told you
what a drag you are?

133
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:55,730
Everyone. Constantly.

134
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:58,107
[Tahani mimics fanfare]

135
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:02,403
I hereby pronounce you King Jason.

136
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:04,197
Dope.

137
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:06,991
Where did you learn how to do this?

138
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:09,410
The Hertfordshire Academy
for Expressionless Girls,

139
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:12,413
a finishing school I attended
before Oxford,

140
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:14,499
and then of course the Sorbonne.

141
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,543
I haven't asked
where you were educated.

142
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,297
I went to Lynyrd Skynyrd High School
in northeast Jacksonville,

143
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:24,133
which was really just a bunch of tugboats
tied together.

144
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,718
Didn't you get seasick?

145
00:06:25,802 --> 00:06:29,347
No, sorry, they were tied together
in a junkyard.

146
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,599
It wasn't a very good school.

147
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:35,228
For most of my classes, we sold
dirty magazines door-to-door.

148
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:39,649
You know, Jason, every single detail
about your life is deeply disturbing.

149
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,567
And yet, I envy you.

150
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:43,986
I was never allowed to goof off.

151
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,907
I never had a friend
I could be myself around.

152
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:49,700
Maybe I can be that friend.

153
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:53,371
Or your husband!

154
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:56,415
-Okay, stop it.
-No, no, no, I'm serious.

155
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,209
Will you marry me?

156
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:03,548
[Eleanor]
I say we just let sleeping dogs lie.

157
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:07,301
Tell Janet Derek can stay,
but she's gotta keep him under wraps,

158
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,262
so no other demons don't find out.

159
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:13,433
Fine. As long as they fly under the radar
and Janet stays happy,

160
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:15,518
I think we'll be safe. Janet?

161
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:17,311
-You always do this!
-You don't respect me

162
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:18,604
and you never have!

163
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,148
You make a federal case out of everything!

164
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:21,941
Because to you, I'll always be
that guy you made!

165
00:07:22,024 --> 00:07:22,859
Guys! What's going on?

166
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:25,445
Can we not do this in front of my friends?

167
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:28,322
So they're your friends now.
I'm stating a fact.

168
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:30,658
They are your friends.
I don't know these people.

169
00:07:30,741 --> 00:07:32,160
I am out of here.

170
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:35,037
-Oh, great, Derek.
-I'm gonna go back to our void

171
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,999
and I'm gonna try and forget
this ever happened.

172
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:40,543
-It is not your void. It is my void!
-Oh. Wow.

173
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,754
I know it's
a boundless, barren nothingness,

174
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,631
but you are always there.

175
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,300
-Fine, I'll go somewhere else.
-Fine!

176
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:49,969
No, not fine! Don't go somewhere else!

177
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:51,304
Okay. Yeah.

178
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,556
We're forked, aren't we?

179
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,350
Look, Jason, you're lovely

180
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:59,854
and I've had a wonderful time
these past few weeks,

181
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,398
but why on Earth would I marry you?

182
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:05,109
Well, for one thing, we're not on Earth.

183
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:06,861
Decent point.

184
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:09,405
Also, we like each other.

185
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:12,950
And I promise to always be nice to you.

186
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:15,328
Okay.

187
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:20,082
I'll marry you. But I need some time
to plan a proper reception.

188
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,000
Where will everyone sit?

189
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:22,835
Michael and Janet
opposite Chidi and Eleanor

190
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:24,378
or Michael and Eleanor opposite
Janet and Chidi?

191
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,380
Let's have it today. At the beach!

192
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,174
The beach is where
all the best stuff happens,

193
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:31,928
like swimsuit issues
and <i>Saving Private Ryan,</i>

194
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:35,181
-and <i>Jersey Shore</i> and crabs!
-Okay.

195
00:08:35,264 --> 00:08:37,558
Oh, I hope Janet's back online.

196
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,519
-Janet?
-Hi, there.

197
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,939
-Is everything all right?
-Yeah.

198
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:45,399
Mmm-hmm. Everything's fine. It's okay.
I'm fine.

199
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:48,069
So it's all fine. [laughs]

200
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:49,737
How can I help you?

201
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:51,072
-Wait. There he is!
-[gasps]

202
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:53,032
Derek. How are you? Nice to meet you.

203
00:08:53,115 --> 00:08:55,117
-Derek, get down!
-Come here!

204
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,954
I am not coming down
because I'm meant to come here.

205
00:08:58,037 --> 00:09:00,957
I came here on purpose
'cause this tree is my new house.

206
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,668
This is Derek's house
and Janet's not allowed in,

207
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:05,294
