216
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,611
How come you never get this upset
at anything I do, Janet?

217
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:32,655
Do not start with me right now, Derek!

218
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:33,656
I will start it.

219
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:35,825
-No, no, no, don't!
-Okay.

220
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:38,911
-Do not avoid me by going to the void!
-No, no, no!

221
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:41,998
-What a little bench!
-[Chidi groans]

222
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:44,250
Things are falling apart here.

223
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:49,380
Chidi, I understand the ethics involved,
but we need to stop that wedding!

224
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:51,882
We break up Jason and Tahani.

225
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:55,595
Janet stops being sad. Derek goes away.

226
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:57,597
Fine, but...

227
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,681
[both groan]

228
00:09:58,764 --> 00:10:00,474
There's something called
the doctrine of double effect.

229
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:04,061
To remain ethical, you can't go into this
with the intention of killing Derek.

230
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:08,232
Your only goal has to be to spare
Jason and Tahani from future pain

231
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,151
by filling them in on Jason's past.

232
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:11,277
No, I got you.

233
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:15,364
So, ethically we should tell Jason
he used to be married to Janet

234
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:19,327
and it would be terrible
if that ultimately led to Derek's death.

235
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,953
-Wink.
-No. Winking is bad.

236
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:23,497
You should not be winking
or saying the word "wink."

237
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:25,833
Okay. We really need to kill...

